title: Jackie: A Tale of Two Sisters
description: Rachael Stirling narrates this multifaceted portrait of former First Lady Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis and her younger sister, Lee Radziwill.

title: Jeremiah Tower: The Last Magnificent
description: This documentary profiles influential chef Jeremiah Tower, who played a pivotal role in the invention of a revolutionary new American cuisine.
actors: Jeremiah Tower, Anthony Bourdain, Mario Batali, Ruth Reichl

title: Jeremy Scott: The People's Designer
description: The journey of fashion designer Jeremy Scott from humble roots on a Missouri farm to creative director of Moschino is charted in this documentary.

title: Jerry Seinfeld: Comedian
description: Christian Charles's documentary follows established comedian Jerry Seinfeld and up-and-comer Orny Adams as they navigate the stand-up circuit.
actors: Jerry Seinfeld, Orny Adams, Colin Quinn, Bill Cosby

title: JFK: The Making of a President
description: Explore how John F. Kennedy's worldview was influenced by his younger years, when he endured poor health, family tragedy and a demanding father.

title: Jim & Andy: The Great Beyond - Featuring a Very Special, Contractually Obligated Mention of Tony Clifton
description: Through the lens of his stunningly immersive performance as Andy Kaufman, Jim Carrey ponders the meaning of life, reality, identity and career.

title: Jimi Hendrix: Voodoo Child
description: Vintage concert footage, personal artifacts and his intimate musings reveal the private side of the life and career of rock-guitar god Jimi Hendrix.

title: Jiro Dreams of Sushi
description: This documentary profiles sushi chef Jiro Ono, an 85-year-old master whose 10-seat, $300-a-plate restaurant is legendary among Tokyo foodies.

title: Joan Didion: The Center Will Not Hold
description: Literary icon Joan Didion reflects on her remarkable career and personal struggles in this intimate documentary directed by her nephew, Griffin Dunne.

title: John Mellencamp: Plain Spoken
description: Part concert film, part documentary, this is a self-narrated musical odyssey that paints an intimate portrait of the celebrated songwriter.

title: Joseph Campbell and the Power of Myth
description: Explore the mind and spirit of teacher and storyteller Joseph Campbell, who discusses the need for modern myths that fit our ever-changing world.

title: Joshua: Teenager vs. Superpower
description: Mobilized by teenage activist Joshua Wong, young citizens of Hong Kong take to the streets in a bid to preserve their history of autonomy from China.

title: Jugaad
description: Following the stories of five diverse individuals, this documentary offers a glimpse into the indomitable tenacity of several Mumbai residents.

title: Justin Bieber: Never Say Never
description: Teen idol Justin Bieber provides personal snapshots from throughout his career, culminating with scenes from his triumphant 2010 concert tour.
actors: Justin Bieber, Ludacris, Usher Raymond, Jaden Smith
